Purpose: Resolve finding L137 (R-2): Add concrete fairness monitoring architecture to Honest Take

[49m[38;5;9m- 135     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m **Regulatory and fairness considerations are not afterthoughts.** If your model's denial predictions correlate with patient demographics in ways that result in differential treatment (e.g., claims for certain patient populations get extra scrutiny), you have a fairness problem even if the model is "just predicting what the payer will do." Monitor model performance across demographic groups. Use bias detection tooling (SHAP subgroup analysis, demographic parity metrics) to detect disparate impact. Ensure that the model's predictions don't result in differential access to care or services.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      135[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Regulatory and fairness considerations are not afterthoughts.** If your model's denial predictions correlate with patient demographics in ways that result in differential treatment (e.g., claims for certain patient populations get extra scrutiny), you have a fairness problem even if the model is "just predicting what the payer will do." Monitor model performance across demographic groups. Use bias detection tooling (SHAP subgroup analysis, demographic parity metrics) to detect disparate impact. Ensure that the model's predictions don't result in differential access to care or services.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      136[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      137[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Concretely, build fairness monitoring into the pipeline from day one. Run a weekly bias detection job (SageMaker Clarify or equivalent) that computes Demographic Parity Difference (DPD) and Disparate Impact (DI) metrics across at least these subgroups: patient age group (pediatric, adult, geriatric), coverage type (commercial, Medicare, Medicaid), place of service, and procedure category (surgical, diagnostic, E/M, behavioral health). Set alerting thresholds: when any subgroup's precision or recall diverges more than 10 percentage points from the population average, trigger an alarm. Generate a quarterly fairness report for compliance review that documents model performance by subgroup, any corrective actions taken (threshold adjustments, feature removals, retraining with balanced sampling), and an attestation that the model's outputs are not creating differential access to care. This report should be reviewed by your compliance officer, not just your ML team.
